Body: Description: After kicking off the SPAC System Scan for SPO, we're getting an invalid URI error. This is post upgrading to NEA v11.6.0.138. Data is successfully being collected by NAM, but NEA seems unable to ingest it.

Steps to Reproduce Updated: 1. Collect data successfully from SPO in NAM
2. Run SPAC System Scan against same NAM monitored SPO host
3. Job fails within 10 minutes, no data ingested

What We've Learned Updated: Issue began after upgrading to NEA v11.6.0.138

Looks like it happens when compressing T2s, but there is no indication in that any logs have been parsed yet.
Next Steps Updated: Sent artifacts to dev for review
Next Steps Updated: R&D reviewing artifacts
Next Steps Updated: R&D reviewing artifacts - priority increased to P1 4/14
Next Steps Updated: Attempted SQL fix from dev but the same error persists. Collected logs and updated dev 4/28
Next Steps Updated: SPAC System Scan is currently running and processing logs - check in Monday to see if the scan completed (there is a backlog of event logs to get through)
